1. Getting command-line arguments
  $ ./me1-1.sh
  Usage: ./me1-1.sh <your-name>

  $ ./me1-1.sh Anne
  Hello Anne!

2. Math expressions
  $ ./me1-2.sh 10 2
  SUM: 12
  DIFF: 8
  PROD: 20
  QUO: 5

3. Using system tools I + processing files in a directory
  $ ./me1-3.sh /path/to/dir 100
  Files with word count < 100:
  myfile-99 (wc: 99) 

4. Using system tools II
  $ ./me1-4.sh 02/14/2018
  02/14/2018 is a Wednesday

5. Using system tools III 
  $ ./me1-5.sh 02/14/2018
  02/14/2018 is a Wednesday
  2 days to go!

